The paper presents a distributed algorithm for computing all-pairs shortest paths in a graph, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The algorithm involves computing a 'blocker set', which is a data structure used in dynamic programming algorithms, and hence could also be classified under data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.DM). The algorithm also involves communication between nodes in the graph, which falls under the category of network protocols and algorithms (cs.NI) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
